{Speech 20}{}{[Wipes the glasses and looks at you suspiciously] And what reason would that be?}
{Speech 20 Answer Exit}{}{Ah, never mind, I was @sex@|mistaken|mistaken|. [Leave]}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{Do you know Dusty?}
{Speech 20 Answer 24}{}{I had a few too many yesterday, Mira...}
{Speech 21}{}{That oaf, from Downtown? Of course I know him, the damn competitor.}
{Speech 21 Answer 22}{}{Well, there you go. That oaf would be very grateful to you if you brought him a few bottles of Rot Gut.}
{Speech 22}{}{No way. He'll manage without!}
{Speech 22 Answer 23}{}{You could secure a partnership down the line...}
{Speech 23}{}{Never! Go to hell!}
{Speech 24}{}{Got a headache, huh? But you don't look too bad.}
{Speech 24 Answer 25}{}{Believe me, my skull isn't just aching. It's about to split open!}
{Speech 25}{}{So what's the problem? Drown your sorrows. Want me to mix you a cocktail?}
{Speech 25 Answer 26}{}{[Shake your head, feigning suffering] Won't help, I know myself. Only a little bottle of Rot Gut can save me. You got any?}
{Speech 26}{}{[Whistles] Well, well. Rot Gut, he wants! I've got only one bottle left. Saving it for an important customer.}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{ What about me? Am I not an important customer?}
{Speech 27}{}{Sorry, of course, but...}
{Speech 27 Answer 28}{}{And you'll just let me, right here in your bar, kick the bucket from a headache?}
{Speech 27 Answer Exit}{}{You're cruel, Mira. [Leave]}
{Speech 28}{}{You're exaggerating. You'll survive somehow. On the other hand... I'll give you the last bottle if you help me deal with Lenny.}
{Speech 28 Answer Exit}{}{The last thing I need with a hangover is damn mutants. [Leave]}
{Speech 28 Answer 29}{}{What's the deal with Lenny?}
{Speech 29}{}{Lenny's all right. He's just getting cocky. Hasn't paid for two days now, says he's a local landmark and ought to drink for free.}
{Speech 29 Answer 30}{}{The nerve!}
{Speech 30}{}{Yeah. I can't lean on him myself, you understand. The locals love him and won't help. But you could.}
{Speech 30 Answer 31}{}{How much does he owe you?}
{Speech 31}{}{300 caps. I'd be grateful if you got them back. And listen, don't be too rough with him, all right?}
{Speech 31 Answer Exit}{}{I'll be Gallantry and Courtesy itself. Nothing will happen to Lenny, and you'll get your money.}
{Speech 31 Answer 32}{}{300? Such a trifle? I'll pay you myself, no problem!}
{Speech 32}{}{Oh! Seriously? Well, that's an option too.}
{Speech 32 Answer Exit}{}{You know, I'll think it over a couple minutes and come back. [Leave]}
{Speech 32 Answer 33}{}{Here's the money, where's my Rot Gut?}
{Speech 33}{}{Take it. Fair and square. Just like I promised.}
{Speech 34}{}{Oh, well, thank you. I was already thinking you'd cheated me. Here's your Rot Gut, though I get the feeling you don't need it anymore.}
{Speech 34 Answer Exit}{}{It'll come in handy tomorrow. Hic! Goodbye!}
{Speech 34 Answer Exit*}{}{It'll come in handy tomorrow. Hic! Goodbye!}
{Speech 34 Answer Exit**}{}{It'll come in handy tomorrow. Hic! Goodbye!}
{Speech 34 Answer Exit***}{}{It'll come in handy tomorrow. Hic! Goodbye!}
{Speech 40}{}{At the moment I've got nothing to offer you.@@When I need your help, I'll let you know.@@Not now.}
{Speech 40 Answer Exit}{}{Got it. I'll drop by later. [Leave]@@You know where to find me if anything comes up. [Leave]@@Too bad. [Leave]}
{Speech 41}{}{Your help would be very welcome. The Bazaar is growing, more and more customers, I need more booze.@@You're just in time. I'm running out of hooch, if you help with deliveries I'd be grateful.@@If you know where to get booze, then we have a deal.}
{Speech 41 Answer 42}{}{What kind of booze do you need?@@What do you need and how much do you pay?@@More specifics! How much, what brands, at what price?}
{Speech 42}{}{I need moonshine and beer. That's the most popular hooch at the Bazaar. I pay 10 caps for beer, 20 for moonshine. I only take it by the batch, 20 bottles.@@Bring me beer and moonshine. I take no less than 20 bottles at a time. Beer - 10 caps, moonshine - 20.@@If you're serious, I need beer and moonshine. Minimum 20 bottles. For beer I'll give 10 caps, for moonshine - 20.}
{Speech 42 Answer Exit}{}{No, this isn't for me. I'm no @sex@|trader|trader| of some kind. [Leave]@@I'm not going to work for peanuts. [Leave]@@No, your offer doesn't interest me. [Leave]}
{Speech 42 Answer Exit*}{}{Got it. As soon as I get the hooch, I'll come back to you. [Leave]@@No problem. I'll be back soon with the goods. [Leave]@@Don't you worry. Your customers won't die of thirst now that @sex@|I'm|I'm| on the job. [Leave]}
{Speech 42 Answer 43}{}{I've got the beer. 20 bottles, minimum batch. [Hand over 20 bottles of beer]@@Beer, then? Take it. [Hand over 20 bottles of beer]@@I was told this is excellent beer. [Hand over 20 bottles of beer]}
{Speech 42 Answer 44}{}{Moonshine. 20 bottles, just as @sex@|I|I| promised. [Hand over 20 bottles of moonshine]@@Will you take the moonshine now, or should I drop by later? [Hand over 20 bottles of moonshine]@@Good moonshine. Tasty! You can't pull it away by the ears! [Hand over 20 bottles of moonshine]}
{Speech 43}{}{Well now, the beer is sorted. Thanks for the cooperation. You can never have too much beer.@@You catch on fast. I'll keep you in mind.@@Thanks, you helped me a lot. These devils guzzle a ton of beer.}
{Speech 43 Answer Exit}{}{Great. If you need more booze, let me know. [Leave]@@Don't mention it. Nobody will die of thirst! [Leave]@@Next time I'll bring a whole tanker of this hooch. [Leave]@@A pleasure doing business with you, Mira. [Leave] It's business. I'm a real businessman! [Wink at Mira and leave]@@The Wrights never dreamed of such a booze delivery service, did they, Mira? [Leave]}
{Speech 44}{}{Thanks. Strong hooch is just what I need in the bar right now.@@Strong drinks at the Bazaar get downed faster than molerats lap up brahmin milk. Thanks for the quick work.@@Yeeee! I knew you wouldn't let me down! Here's your pay. [Hands over money]}
{Speech 44 Answer Exit}{}{Great. If you need more booze, let me know. [Leave]@@Don't mention it. Nobody will die of thirst! [Leave]@@Next time I'll bring a whole tanker of this hooch. [Leave]@@A pleasure doing business with you, Mira. [Leave] It's business. I'm a real businessman! [Wink at Mira and leave]@@The Wrights never dreamed of such a booze delivery service, did they, Mira? [Leave]}
{Speech 50}{}{[Winces] Ugh, what a scarecrow. I've got no work for you!@@Go away, go away. There's nothing I can do for you.}
{Speech 50 Answer Exit}{}{[Make a sad face] Me leave! You no like! [Leave]@@Me get upset. You be sorry. [Leave]}
{Speech 51}{}{Hm. Maybe there's some use in you after all. All right, here's the deal. Bring me a crate! A CRATE! Got it? C-R-A-T-E! of empty bottles, and I'll pay you 100 caps.}
{Speech 51 Answer 52}{}{One? Yeah-yeah! [Turn to leave]}
{Speech 52}{}{Damn! Not one! A CRATE! 20 of them. 4 times as many as you've got fingers on your hand. [Waves a hand with spread fingers in your face]}
{Speech 52 Answer Exit}{}{WOW! Nuh-uh! Many! Too much!! [Leave]}
{Speech 52 Answer Exit*}{}{[Consider whether it'd be easier to chop off the extra fingers so you don't have to carry so many bottles] Oh! Me bring! Wait!}
{Speech 52 Answer 53}{}{Me bring bottles! [Drop the bottles on the floor]}
{Speech 53}{}{[The crash of breaking glass rings out] Devil! What an oaf you are! You broke half of them!! Fine, take the money and get out!}
{Speech 53 Answer Exit}{}{Ha! Money! Mine! [Leave]}
